1️⃣ Login Page in Filament

After installing Filament and creating an admin user, you will access the panel like this:

http://localhost:8000/admin

When you open this, Filament will automatically show a login page.

Example flow:

User opens /admin
        ↓
Login page appears
        ↓
User enters email + password
        ↓
Dashboard opens

So you do not need to build login manually.

2️⃣ How the First User Will Be Created

Before logging in, you need to create the first admin user.

Run this command:

php artisan make:filament-user

Terminal will ask:

Name:
Email:
Password:

Example:

Name: Admin
Email: admin@gmail.com
Password: 12345678

After this, the admin user will be saved in the users table.

Now you can login.

3️⃣ How Other Users Will Be Created

After admin logs in:

http://localhost:8000/admin

Admin can open:

Users → Create User

Then create users like:

Name	Email	Role
John	john@mail.com
	Seller
Rahul	rahul@mail.com
	Buyer

So registration is handled by admin, not by public users.

This is how most admin systems work in companies.

4️⃣ How Login Will Work in Your System

Example:

Admin
Email: admin@mail.com
Role: Admin

Admin sees:

Users
Roles
Sellers
Buyers
Items
Sales
P&L
Seller
Email: seller@mail.com
Role: Seller

Seller sees:

Items
Sales
Buyer
Email: buyer@mail.com
Role: Buyer

Buyer sees:

Items

This happens because of database-driven menu access.

5️⃣ So Do You Need Registration Page?

❌ No public registration page needed.

Your system will work like this:

Admin creates users
        ↓
Users login through Filament
        ↓
Roles control what they can see
